1
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:05,200
My name's Pete.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:06,800
And I'm an alcoholic.

3
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:10,800
I used to be the best
stickup man in North Philly.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:12,300
It's no joke.

5
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:14,600
Wasn't nothing I couldn't rob.

6
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:16,800
Let you in on a secret.

7
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:18,600
It's not the gun.

8
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:20,000
It's the attitude.

9
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:22,900
I'd look
in my victims' eyes.

10
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:24,400
Talk to 'em real quiet.

11
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,900
Remind 'em what's on the line
if they play hero.

12
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,600
They'd never have
another Christmas,

13
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:31,400
never hear their wife
laugh again.

14
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,700
Never hold their children.

15
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:36,300
No problem after that.

16
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:38,700
Eh, that's not me anymore.

17
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:43,800
Been inside 12 years.

18
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,500
Sober every one of them.

19
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,800
Wasn't easy.

20
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:49,000
A lot of time
to worry on my mistakes.

21
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:51,900
This kept me going.

22
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,200
Letter from my kid
when he was five years old.

23
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:55,600
Caught the football
for the first time.

24
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,900
Only I wasn't the one
who threw it to him.

25
00:00:58,300 --> 00:01:00,800
All I could do,
write him back.

26
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,400
Which I done consistent.

27
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:06,600
I haven't heard back
in a while.

28
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:08,500
Don't blame him.

29
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:09,400
Kid's got a life.

30
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,500
Proud of that.

31
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,700
I'm gettin' out today.

32
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:15,600
Goin' back to my son.

33
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:16,900
Got a job lined up.

34
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:18,400
Gonna do it right this time.

35
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,400
God granted me
a second chance.

36
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,500
I'm takin' it.

37
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,100
Check out the looky-loo.

38
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:20,500
Narcs's too busy

39
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:23,300
congratulating themselves
to clean up for us.

40
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,500
Hey, get lost, buddy.

41
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,500
This is
a crime scene.

42
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:27,900
Yeah. Mine.

43
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,800
But you have my permission
to stay, Cagney.

44
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:36,500
I never heard
that one before, Serpico.

45
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:38,100
Touch?

46
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,400
Who's the jackass?

47
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:44,600
Eddie Saccardo.

48
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,200
Runs the narcotics
task force.

49
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,100
This is his bust.

50
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,200
Heard of him.

51
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,800
Keyed in on every corner
in Philly.

52
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,100
They say he knows
the crime goin' down

53
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:53,200
- before the crook does.
- Yeah, regular Superman,

54
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,200
this guy.

55
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,200
Know the name Pete Doyle?

56
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,000
Fugitive. Pulled his
prints off five guns

57
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,200
with murders to match
ten years ago.

58
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:01,700
Could never track him
until now.

59
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:03,800
- This him?
