That's my gimmick.

66
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,300
"The man with the hand. "

67
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,800
- Catchy.
- Yeah.

68
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:06,300
I wanted to get one of those
voodoo guys to shrink it for me,

69
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:07,900
so I could wear it
around my neck.

70
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,500
Your boss said I could observe.

71
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:11,900
That's my drug dealer.

72
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,000
Where's the rest of Pete Doyle?

73
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:15,700
Guy that belongs to that hand.

74
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:16,300
Assume he owed you money.

75
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,600
Double-crossed you.

76
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,800
That's why
you killed him.

77
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:19,700
No, he didn't kill Pete.

78
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:21,200
- I didn't kill him.
- You found him.

79
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,400
- I found him.
- Where?

80
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:25,000
Fifth street.
Past Lehigh.

81
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,700
Used to run a corner over there.

82
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,200
I used to run a corner
back there.

83
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,000
When was this?

84
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,400
About ten years ago.
Fall, I think.

85
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:32,400
It was chilly.

86
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,000
I'm on my way to work.

87
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,300
There it is.

88
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:37,200
- The hand.
- The whole body.

89
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,200
Couldn't leave the guy
on the corner.

90
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:49,600
Bad for business.

91
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:51,700
Mmm, decide the right thing
to do is saw off the hand?

92
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:53,300
He wasn't needin' it
no more.

93
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:57,300
You know how much I made selling
fingerprints off that thing?

94
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,600
What about the gun?

95
00:04:58,700 --> 00:04:59,700
Keep that, too?

96
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,400
Hell no.

97
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,600
It had a body on it.

98
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,200
I sold the gun.

99
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:04,900
Kept the hand.

100
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,400
Duh.

101
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,300
What do we have
on Pete Doyle?

102
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,600
Besides the fact he's favoring

103
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,700
his left hand?

104
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,800
Some kind
of stickup man

105
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,600
in North Philly.

106
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,200
Uh, Pistol Pete was

107
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,500
the stickup man.

108
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,200
Had real corner
appeal.

109
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:21,200
Neighborhood
loved him.

110
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,600
Always good for
a couple bucks.

111
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,800
Real Jesse James type.

112
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,900
Went away for armed
robbery in '85.

113
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:28,300
Got pinched busting a check
cashing joint. North Kensington.

114
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:29,800
Arresting officer caught him
with the cash

115
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,600
and a.44 Smith & Wesson.

116
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,900
Pete's weapon
of choice.

117
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,500
20-year sentence.

118
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,300
Served 12.

119
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:36,500
Good behavior.

120
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,300
You memorize his rap sheet?

121
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:40,200
No, we used to date.

122
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:43,200
So Pete gets out
September '97.

123
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,800
Ends up dead
a few weeks later.

124
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,300
He might have pissed
someone off.

125
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,600
Says here he had a partner.
Tommy Connell.

126
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:49,800
Career jag-off.

127
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:51,300
You'll find him
at The Tap House.

128
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:53,300
Polluting the same stool
for 20 years.

129
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,000
Pete also had
an ex.

130
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,100
Jules Murphy.

131
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,500
Used to be
a party girl.

132
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,700
Pete knocked her up.

133
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,200
Then he had the nerve

134
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,100
to get put away.
Hear she holds a grudge.

135
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:03,500
What's the matter?
It's not in your file?

136
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,400
I'll pick up
Tommy Connell.

137
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:10,000
Guess I'll pay
the ex a visit.

138
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:22,000
Why are you
still here?

139
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:23,800
Waiting to take possession
of my drug dealer.

140
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,600
Well, we'll call you
when we're done.

141
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:33,900
Been waiting
for the day

142
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:36,100
you'd arrive,
tell me Pete's dead.

143
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:39,600
Pete did a number on you, Jules.

144
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:43,100
Left you high and dry
with a kid to boot.

145
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:44,900
You won't get
an argument out of me.

146
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,900
But I didn't kill him.

147
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:49,500
He was my first love.

148
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,400
Real sweet.

149
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,200
Yeah, he could be.
Charming, too.

150
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,200
Part of him, at least.

151
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:56,100
- The other part didn't care about no one or nothing. 
- Not even your kid?

152
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:59,300
Uh, Petey Jr.

153
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:00,700
Way he saw it,

154
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:03,000
family got in the way
of his "career. "

155
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,800
But that kid
adored the man.

156
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,000
Must have been tough
when Pete went away.

157
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,600
I was left
to fend for myself.

158
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,200
Lot of resentment there.

159
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,600
I was too busy raising my boy.

160
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:16,000
That's when we got together.

161
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,400
Tried to make a good home
for Petey.

162
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,800
Yeah. And we did.

163
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:21,900
So,

164
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,100
Pete comes back.

165
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:26,000
Discovers his son's
got a new dad...

166
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,900
The nerve.

167
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:28,500
Don't see him
for 12 years.

168
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,600
An hour after he's released,
he's on our doorstep.

169
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:35,100
Girard to North Sixth,
cut over on Spring.

170
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:36,900
No...

171
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:38,600
he told me you
know this town.

172
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,300
No, you're going
to be blocked up.

173
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,200
See you readin'
that book.

174
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,100
Like it got the answers
to everything.

175
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,100
I used to read a lot
of those crime books.

176
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,700
Pass the time.

177
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,700
You're him, aren't you?

178
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,800
My dad.

179
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:54,800
Yeah.

180
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,100
You're in jail.

181
00:07:58,300 --> 00:07:59,300
Not anymore.

182
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,500
What? You escape?

183
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:01,500
No.

184
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,200
Done my time.

185
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,900
I'm free.

186
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:10,800
Got it when I was your age.

187
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:13,200
My declaration of independence.

188
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:15,800
You got any tattoos?

189
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,300
That was a joke.

190
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:24,600
I got you somethin'.

191
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,200
Your favorite.

192
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,900
Told me about it
in one of your letters.

193
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:35,400
I was five.

194
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,800
I play soccer now.

195
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,500
I didn't know.

196
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,600
It's okay.

197
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,400
I've had a lot a time to think.

198
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,700
I'm not standin' here
expectin' the world to stop

199
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:51,800
now I'm back.
You got a life.

200
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,500
Only hope maybe
I can be a part of it,

201
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,800
if that's okay with you.

202
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:01,400
Get in the house, Petey.

203
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,200
Jules.

204
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:11,200
You look great.

205
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,900
I know, you're pissed.

206
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:14,900
Don't worry.

207
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,300
I dried up inside. Got my GED.

208
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:18,400
I'm committed to doin' right

209
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,900
- by you and Petey.
- You think

210
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:21,600
you can just drop by?

211
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,500
Not even the courtesy
to let us know?

212
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:24,600
I meant to.

213
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,000
I kept tryin'
to put pen to paper.

214
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,700
Explain it all. Nothin' came.

215
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:31,600
But I told Petey.

216
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,500
Last couple letters.

217
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,500
Petey didn't get your letters.

218
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:37,400
I kinda figured.

219
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,400
Leave us be, Pete.

220
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,900
Honestly, for the sake
of the boy, it'd be better

221
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:49,600
if you're still
in jail.

222
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,400
Never came back after that.

223
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,400
Only good thing he did:
staying away.

224
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,100
Petey Jr. ever go looking
for his dad?

225
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,100
Seek out the hero?

226
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:07,800
Kept his eye
on the prize.

227
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,500
College, a real job.

228
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,500
Never mentioned
Pete again.

229
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,500
Tommy Connell,
Pete Doyle's wingman.

230
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:21,200
You're a real
sweetheart, Tommy.

231
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,500
Been reading your record.

232
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,600
You can read?

233
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,500
Ooh. Laugh riot.

234
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,100
You and Pete
pulled some

235
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:32,900
crazy jobs back in the day.

236
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:35,200
Oh, the nostalgia file.

237
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:37,200
That's 20 years ago.

238
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:40,200
- Don't got nothing recent?
- What about Pete Doyle's murder?

239
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,200
I heard about that.

240
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,400
It's a damn shame.

241
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,200
You can do better
than that, Tommy.

242
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:47,900
I took it as a blow.

243
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,700
- We was like brothers, me and Pete. 
- He went down hard

244
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:53,400
for that check-cashing heist
back in '85.

245
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:55,000
We know you were the second man.

246
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,400
Could've got five years
had he gave you up.

247
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,000
Did 12 instead.

248
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:00,700
Real stand-up guy.

249
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:03,100
So maybe Pete starts thinking
you owe him.

250
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:04,500
You figure it's easier

251
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:05,900
to clear the books.

252
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,800
If what you were

253
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,000
saying was true,

254
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,700
and I admit nothing,

255
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,600
I'd have been grateful.

256
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,200
One way of looking
at it.

257
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:16,000
Other way, a debt like that
becomes a burden

258
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,400
- hanging over your head.
- Shows what you know.

259
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,600
I did everything
I could to help when he got out,

260
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,100
but he wouldn't accept.

261
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,700
This was a different Pete Doyle
than the one I knew.

262
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:32,800
I've been calling and calling.

263
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,700
Your cousin
was my counselor inside.

264
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:36,200
Said you hired guys like me.

265
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,100
Used to.

266
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,700
I got burned too many times.

267
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,600
Not by me.
I'm a man of my word.

268
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,800
I'll work straight commission.

269
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:42,600
I got an aptitude.

270
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,800
It's win-win.

271
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,600
All I want's a chance.

272
