kid of yours.

295
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,000
Comes by the place.
We talk about the old days.

296
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,400
He loves those stories.

297
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,700
I don't want you talking to him.

298
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:44,800
Serious.

299
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:47,200
He's a good kid.
You stay the hell away.

300
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:51,800
Catch you next time.

301
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,400
But I ain't worried.

302
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,600
I know the real
Pete Doyle's in there.

303
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:57,800
You have him come see me
when he's ready.

304
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,100
Expect us to believe
he went straight?

305
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,500
As a frickin' arrow.

306
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:04,500
Wanted a regular job,

307
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,800
regular life.

308
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:07,700
Didn't matter.

309
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:09,100
Got him killed anyway.

310
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:12,000
Pete Doyle checked in weekly
