Your mom know you're here?

373
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,400
You shouldn't disobey her.

374
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,200
I know.
You're my dad.

375
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,500
I should get a say.

376
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:05,100
Wow. This is where

377
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:07,200
you beat up that
group of Marines.

378
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,200
Tommy told me the story.

379
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:11,900
You shouldn't put too much stock
in his version.

380
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,000
It was one guy.

381
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,200
You need to get
out of here.

382
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,900
They got rules about underage.

383
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:22,700
You saved them.

384
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:24,700
The letters I sent.

385
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:25,900
You kept them.

386
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,300
Every one.

387
00:16:28,100 --> 00:16:29,500
Kept me alive in there.

388
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,100
So how come
you never wrote back?

389
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,900
Hey, mop boy!

390
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,400
Go home, Petey.

391
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,600
Well, if it ain't Pistol Pete.

392
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,400
I heard you were out.

393
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,500
You remember me?

394
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:56,200
Officer O'Leary.

395
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,100
Guy who put your
worthless ass away.

396
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:04,300
Hey, watch the shoes.

397
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,300
My good pair.

398
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,500
Nice gig you got here.

399
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:13,400
Sure you working
some scheme on the side.

400
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,100
I'm out of the game.

401
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,000
I told you to watch

402
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,700
the damn shoes.

403
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:25,900
Dad?

404
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,100
Well, hell, Pete.

405
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:29,700
You got a son.

406
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,400
Little thug in training.

407
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,800
It's in the blood, right?

408
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,300
Get out of here, Petey. Go.

409
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:36,700
Yeah, run along, Petey.

410
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:39,000
Sure I'll be locking
you up real soon.

411
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,100
Give you one of my famous
tours of the city.

412
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:42,400
Remember those, Pete?

413
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:43,500
Think the kid'll take

414
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:44,900
to it like you did?

415
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:47,800
Do it. I'm begging you.

416
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:00,700
You'll slip up.

417
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,200
And when you do,
I'll be there.

418
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,600
And we'll settle this.

419
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,300
The way he just took it.

420
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,700
Kept cleaning up
after that jerk.

421
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:32,000
It was humiliating.

422
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,900
Your pop was supposed
to be larger than life,

423
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:36,700
but he was just a man.

424
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:38,000
No, he was a coward.

425
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,200
And a liar.

426
00:18:40,900 --> 00:18:42,500
Best thing he ever did,

427
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:44,900
disappearing from my life.

428
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:56,400
How's retirement
treating you, Dan?

429
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:58,300
Living the dream, John.

430
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:01,200
Only have to work two jobs
to cover my alimony.

431
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,400
But that's not why I'm here.

432
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:05,700
It's about Pete Doyle.

433
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:06,800
Detective Miller.

434
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,400
I heard you
found his hand.

435
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:12,100
I only wish I was there
to see it come off.

436
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:13,300
Kind of harsh.

437
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,500
You know how Pistol Pete
got his name, sugar?

438
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:17,500
His first robbery.

439
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,200
Liquor store.

440
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,200
He pistol-whips the salesman.

441
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:22,500
Cracked his head open.

442
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,000
Guy's in a coma
for a month.

443
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,600
Pete was 15.

444
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,700
He'd kill you
as much as look at you.

445
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:30,400
Maybe you did it first?

446
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:30,900
You threatened

447
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:33,400
Pete Doyle in a bar
full of customers.

448
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:36,200
I told him I was waiting
for him to slip up.

449
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:37,400
Which I was.

450
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,100
John, tell her what it was like

451
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:42,400
when cops actually
did police work.

452
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:44,600
Like your famous
tour of the city?

453
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:45,800
Take 'em out to the river,

454
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,300
show 'em the business end
of your nightstick.

455
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:49,600
You know, I'm not going
to explain myself.

456
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:52,200
I had a job.
I did it good.

457
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:54,200
Way we heard it, it was personal

