00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:07,620
Please. Excuse me.

74
00:24:11,870 --> 00:24:13,410
That ain't right, bringin' him here.

75
00:24:13,580 --> 00:24:14,720
You shouldn't do that to a guy.

76
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:16,190
Tell me about Pete,Tommy.

77
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:17,410
You two were planning a robbery.

78
00:24:17,580 --> 00:24:18,380
I want to make a deal first.

79
00:24:18,550 --> 00:24:20,020
All we care about is Pete's murder.

80
00:24:20,180 --> 00:24:21,730
Complete immunity then in writing.

81
00:24:21,890 --> 00:24:25,240
I could bring Saccardo back in to discuss that with you.

82
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:28,850
All right. Point made.

83
00:24:29,020 --> 00:24:30,820
I knew it had to be the right job

84
00:24:30,980 --> 00:24:32,410
to get Pete back to work.

85
00:24:32,590 --> 00:24:34,860
Something... choice.

86
00:24:35,030 --> 00:24:36,780
Still took a lot of convincing,

87
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,560
but he changed his mind.

88
00:24:38,730 --> 00:24:40,660
Why'd he finally give in?

89
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:42,930
I had an ace in the hole.

90
00:24:48,770 --> 00:24:50,730
I'm ain't gonna lie to you.

91
00:24:50,890 --> 00:24:53,290
This is ambitious.

92
00:24:53,670 --> 00:24:55,400
It's probably the biggest score

93
00:24:55,570 --> 00:24:56,550
we ever had.

94
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,160
We're talkin' a bank?

95
00:24:58,330 --> 00:25:00,690
All will be revealed in due course.

96
00:25:00,850 --> 00:25:04,250
Drink your beer. I'm on the wagon.

97
00:25:06,410 --> 00:25:08,290
I figure we go in heavy.

98
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:10,660
Shotguns blazing, kneecap one of the guards.

99
00:25:10,830 --> 00:25:12,190
Show 'em we mean business.

100
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,980
And if the guy dies, that's felony murder.

101
00:25:15,140 --> 00:25:16,800
Guaranteed life.

102
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,600
I don't intend to get caught.

103
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:20,780
I didn't,either.

104
00:25:21,810 --> 00:25:23,600
You got to understand these guards:

105
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:26,600
whatever they're protecting doesn't belong to them.

106
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:28,310
End of the day, they want to go home.

107
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:33,130
Let 'em know there's no profit for dead heroes.

108
00:25:33,890 --> 00:25:35,150
Damn!

109
00:25:35,310 --> 00:25:37,910
My man is back.

110
00:25:39,470 --> 00:25:41,300
Now will you tell me what the score is?

111
00:25:43,020 --> 00:25:46,510
Hmm. Why don't you ask the brains of the operation?

112
00:25:50,580 --> 00:25:53,630
You should see the look on your face.

113
00:25:53,780 --> 00:25:54,730
You put him up to it?

114
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:56,460
It was my idea.

115
00:25:56,630 --> 00:25:58,080
Kid worked the whole thing out.

116
00:25:58,240 --> 00:26:00,460
Just like his old man.

117
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:05,990
Hmm? What are you thinking?

118
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:07,660
You're better than this.

119
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:09,390
You're smart. You got a future.

120
00:26:09,550 --> 00:26:11,280
As what,a bus driver? Yeah.

121
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:12,070
An office worker?

122
00:26:12,230 --> 00:26:13,830
Yeah. I don't want that.

123
00:26:14,010 --> 00:26:18,170
I want this with or without you.

124
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:20,400
Guess that's settled then.

125
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:22,810
Let's have a drink,hmm?

126
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:25,730
To the future.

127
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:41,410
Pete let his 15-year-old son participate

128
00:26:41,580 --> 00:26:42,480
in an armed robbery?

129
00:26:42,650 --> 00:26:45,160
Wasn't any older when his cherry broke.

130
00:26:45,320 --> 00:26:47,510
What was the score,Tommy?

131
00:26:47,670 --> 00:26:49,420
Hey,you don't think Junior did his dad?

132
00:26:49,580 --> 00:26:50,930
That'd be messed up.

133
00:26:51,090 --> 00:26:52,830
What was the score?

134
00:26:53,330 --> 00:26:55,910
Gosh,Detective,

135
00:26:56,070 --> 00:26:58,630
it was so long ago...

136
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:02,110
Lawyer's here.

137
00:27:13,580 --> 00:27:14,200
Don't talk

138
00:27:14,390 --> 00:27:16,240
to a suspect of mine without asking again.

139
00:27:16,410 --> 00:27:17,660
He gave you what you wanted,

140
00:27:17,810 --> 00:27:18,900
didn't he? Until his lawyer showed up.

141
00:27:19,060 --> 00:27:21,650
I'm not the one who called him.

142
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:24,420
My desk. My bad.

143
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:26,270
The guy you mentioned in there,

144
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:28,350
uh,who freaked Tommy out.

145
00:27:28,510 --> 00:27:29,750
Phil the Pill?

146
00:27:29,910 --> 00:27:30,580
Who is he?

147
00:27:30,750 --> 00:27:32,450
Friend of Tommy's from the block.

148
00:27:32,620 --> 00:27:34,590
Kind of famous for his bad luck.

149
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:36,430
Arrested him one time up on this roof.

150
00:27:36,590 --> 00:27:40,120
Guy tried to run from me, fell off,crippled himself.

151
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:41,440
Hmm. Like I said,bad luck.

152
00:27:41,610 --> 00:27:43,440
He fell off?

153
00:27:43,820 --> 00:27:46,430
That's how the story goes.

154
00:27:49,290 --> 00:27:51,890
You got to try these ribs.

155
00:28:02,150 --> 00:28:03,830
You lied to us,Petey.

156
00:28:04,010 --> 00:28:05,150
Said you never saw your father

157
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:07,680
after that time at the bar.

158
00:28:07,850 --> 00:28:08,910
I didn't.

159
00:28:09,090 --> 00:28:10,110
Lying again.

160
00:28:10,290 --> 00:28:12,570
We know why you brought the gun to school.

161
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:14,230
Wasn't to prove a point.

162
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:15,390
For armed robbery.

163
00:28:15,550 --> 00:28:17,720
The family business.

164
00:28:19,380 --> 00:28:21,380
Talked to Tommy,huh?

165
00:28:21,550 --> 00:28:22,240
Made you out to be

166
00:28:22,420 --> 00:28:24,720
some kind of criminal mastermind.

167
00:28:24,890 --> 00:28:26,690
Ready to put his hand on the Bible,

168
00:28:26,860 --> 00:28:28,650
say you're the triggerman.

169
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:29,710
We're givi you a chance

170
00:28:29,890 --> 00:28:32,180
to get out in front of this thing.

171
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:34,580
The day of the robbery,

172
00:28:35,420 --> 00:28:37,360
I was with Pete in the car.

173
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:39,420
It's all right,Petey.

174
00:28:39,590 --> 00:28:40,900
You idolized your father.

175
00:28:41,060 --> 00:28:41,910
Wanted to be him.

176
00:28:42,070 --> 00:28:43,990
You brought him the score.

177
00:28:44,140 --> 00:28:46,100
Figured you'd earned your right at the table,

178
00:28:46,270 --> 00:28:48,560
your father's respect, but something went wrong.

179
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:49,710
Something did,Petey,

180
00:28:49,870 --> 00:28:50,850
'cause he ended up dead.

181
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:54,280
I wasn't looking for his respect.

182
00:28:54,450 --> 00:28:57,650
I was lookin' for a reason to respect him.

183
00:28:57,820 --> 00:28:59,450
He was pathetic.

184
00:28:59,620 --> 00:29:01,300
Cleaning up after drunks,

185
00:29:01,460 --> 00:29:03,020
getting pushed around.

186
00:29:03,180 --> 00:29:03,990
I wanted him

187
00:29:04,160 --> 00:29:05,670
to be the man

188
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:09,250
that I had heard about growing up.

189
00:29:10,550 --> 00:29:12,810
I wanted to believe.

190
00:29:22,470 --> 00:29:24,240
Give me that.

191
00:29:33,370 --> 00:29:35,200
Ready to use it?

192
00:29:35,850 --> 00:29:37,010
Yeah.

193
00:29:40,150 --> 00:29:41,910
Point it at me.

194
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:43,450
Do it.

195
00:29:43,610 --> 00:29:45,270
Like this?

196
00:29:48,820 --> 00:29:50,240
Look me in the eye now.

197
00:29:50,390 --> 00:29:51,330
Show me you're willing to go all the way,

198
00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:54,130
squeeze that trigger, put my brains on the windshield.

199
00:29:54,290 --> 00:29:56,760
I'm a man. I can do it.

200
00:30:07,630 --> 00:30:08,270
You think you're tough?

201
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:09,350
Some kind of

202
00:30:09,510 --> 00:30:09,950
rd man,'cause you gave us

203
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:10,740
a street address?

204
00:30:10,910 --> 00:30:13,410
Wrote down a time? Please stop.

205
00:30:13,570 --> 00:30:14,850
It means nothing.

206
00:30:15,020 --> 00:30:17,230
You mean nothing. Dad...

207
00:30:17,330 --> 00:30:19,150
Want to know why I never wrote you letters?

208
00:30:19,310 --> 00:30:21,030
'Cause you weren't worth the effort.

209
00:30:21,190 --> 00:30:23,290
You have zero to offer.

210
00:30:23,460 --> 00:30:25,840
Get out of here!

211
00:30:32,340 --> 00:30:34,300
Truck's right on time.

212
00:30:34,470 --> 00:30:36,710
What's up with the kid?

213
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:38,720
Forget about him.

214
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:41,250
Let's do this.

215
00:30:52,900 --> 00:30:55,110
Your stepdad drove an armored car?

216
00:30:55,260 --> 00:30:56,290
I told Pete everything.

217
00:30:56,460 --> 00:30:59,550
I told him the,uh, the delivery route,

218
00:30:59,710 --> 00:31:03,770
how the guards orated, how much money there was.

219
00:31:03,930 --> 00:31:06,440
I got screwed.

220
00:31:06,590 --> 00:31:07,560
You consider

221
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:11,260
what would have happened if he hadn't cut you out?

222
00:31:11,880 --> 00:31:14,420
What happened to the heist?

223
00:31:14,580 --> 00:31:15,520
It fell apart.

224
00:31:15,700 --> 00:31:16,820
Bernie called the cops.

225
00:31:16,980 --> 00:31:20,560
Did he know who was robbing him?

226
00:31:23,670 --> 00:31:28,410
A few weeks after her stepson's ex-con dad shows up...

227
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:29,350
Bernie's armored car

228
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:31,220
gets hit.

229
00:31:31,390 --> 00:31:32,880
Bernie's a smart guy.

230
00:31:33,050 --> 00:31:36,580
Must have considered Pistol Pete Doyle was involved.

231
00:31:36,740 --> 00:31:40,230
???

232
00:31:50,420 --> 00:31:52,750
d You're a modest guy,Bernie.

233
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:54,710
Way you dress...

234
00:31:54,990 --> 00:31:57,260
...your attitude.

235
00:31:57,950 --> 00:32:00,080
Unassuming.

236
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:02,770
I was in your house the other day.

237
00:32:03,090 --> 00:32:05,120
Had no idea I was sitting across

238
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:06,070
from a hero.

239
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:09,880
Single-handedly thwarted the robbery of your armored car.

240
00:32:10,060 --> 00:32:11,150
I don't talk about it.

241
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:12,850
Well,it was brave.

242
00:32:13,010 --> 00:32:14,880
Fighting off two masked gunmen.

243
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:16,430
Yeah,got a commendation from the company.

244
00:32:16,580 --> 00:32:17,820
Even offered you a reward.

245
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:18,990
You turned them down.

246
00:32:19,170 --> 00:32:20,830
Didn't think it was right,

247
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:22,660
gettin' extra for doing my job.

248
00:32:22,830 --> 00:32:23,680
Oh.

249
00:32:24,930 --> 00:32:26,250
Two weeks later,you quit.

250
00:32:26,420 --> 00:32:28,150
Yeah. Was it the danger?

251
00:32:28,310 --> 00:32:30,280
Comin' so close to dyin'?

252
00:32:30,450 --> 00:32:31,640
Or was it guilt,

253
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:32,650
Bernie,for what happened that day

254
00:32:32,830 --> 00:32:35,400
with Pete and Petey Jr.?

255
00:32:36,470 --> 00:32:38,470
Put this on me all you want.

256
00:32:38,650 --> 00:32:39,570
Leave Petey Jr. out.

257
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:40,970
You knew who was robbing you.

258
00:32:41,140 --> 00:32:43,760
That Petey Jr. must have helped set it up.

259
00:32:43,940 --> 00:32:46,340
Question is why you never told.

260
00:32:46,510 --> 00:32:48,800
I was looking out for the boy.

261
00:32:49,890 --> 00:32:51,860
I could see the change in him when his dad came back.

262
00:32:52,030 --> 00:32:53,780
He was spinning in place.

263
00:32:53,950 --> 00:32:55,480
You raised him like your own.

264
00:32:55,650 --> 00:33:00,000
Tried to teach him right from wrong,best I could.

265
00:33:01,010 --> 00:33:01,910
To be decent.

266
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:04,580
And Pete- he was the wrong kind of influence.

267
00:33:04,740 --> 00:33:07,010
Petey Jr. ate it up.

268
00:33:07,180 --> 00:33:08,380
Adored that man.

269
00:33:08,550 --> 00:33:10,420
Romanticized him.

270
00:33:10,580 --> 00:33:11,860
I had to do somethin'.

271
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:14,750
Did you chase after him, take his gun?

272
00:33:14,910 --> 00:33:16,410
Shoot him down for Petey Jr. 's sake?

273
00:33:16,570 --> 00:33:20,480
I would have if it had come to that.

274
00:33:20,740 --> 00:33:22,850
But it played out different.

275
00:33:32,370 --> 00:33:34,390
All clear.

276
00:33:48,300 --> 00:33:49,520
Give me the gun. Don't even think it.

277
00:33:49,690 --> 00:33:51,360
Give me the gun. Drop it!

278
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:54,610
Don't do it. Drop your gun. Drop it right now.

279
00:33:54,780 --> 00:33:55,730
Drop it!

280
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:58,010
Get out of the truck. Get out of the truck!

281
00:33:58,180 --> 00:34:00,770
Put your hands on the dash.

282
00:34:00,940 --> 00:34:02,910
Nothing stupid.

283
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:08,140
I think we hit the jackpot.

284
00:34:11,220 --> 00:34:15,250
I said, "I think we hit the jackpot. "

285
00:34:15,610 --> 00:34:18,010
I think we hit the jackpot now.

286
00:34:18,170 --> 00:34:19,610
Get on your knees.

287
00:34:19,770 --> 00:34:21,410
Come on, on your knees.

288
00:34:30,130 --> 00:34:31,240
I'm gonna need you to do something.

289
00:34:31,420 --> 00:34:32,980
I'm gonna need you to hit whatever panic button you got

290
00:34:33,150 --> 00:34:34,800
in here.

291
00:34:34,960 --> 00:34:36,970
Yeah,I do it,you starshooting. Ha.

292
00:34:37,140 --> 00:34:38,340
Usually,I'd be giving you all the reasons

293
00:34:38,510 --> 00:34:39,750
why you shouldn't act,

294
00:34:39,930 --> 00:34:41,640
but this is going to get bloody real soon.

295
00:34:41,810 --> 00:34:44,740
You ain't fricking listening!

296
00:34:44,900 --> 00:34:46,390
You got the boy to consider.

297
00:34:46,560 --> 00:34:47,660
Think about Petey.

298
00:34:47,830 --> 00:34:50,150
He's at a rocky age.

299
00:34:51,210 --> 00:34:52,750
He needs the right guidance.

300
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:53,960
That's on you.

301
00:34:54,130 --> 00:34:55,120
Why are you doing this,Pete?

302
00:34:55,300 --> 00:34:57,260
Just do it.

303
00:35:04,380 --> 00:35:06,360
You take care of him,okay?

304
00:35:07,790 --> 00:35:09,750
You're his dad now.

305
00:35:10,330 --> 00:35:12,110
What the hell?!

306
00:35:22,610 --> 00:35:24,180
Cops pinned it on a couple pros

307
00:35:24,350 --> 00:35:25,860
who got killed in some other robbery attempt

308
00:35:26,030 --> 00:35:27,970
a few weeks later.

309
00:35:28,150 --> 00:35:30,050
You didn't set them straight.

310
00:35:30,230 --> 00:35:32,630
Would have brought up a whole bunch of questions.

311
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:35,180
Petey didn't need this hanging over him.

312
00:35:35,350 --> 00:35:38,470
Cards he was playing- convict dad and all-

313
00:35:38,630 --> 00:35:39,910
he had enough to deal with.

314
00:35:40,080 --> 00:35:41,960
Pete kept saying...

315
00:35:42,590 --> 00:35:44,330
"We hit the jackpot. "

316
00:35:44,510 --> 00:35:45,360
What'd he mean by that?

317
00:35:45,540 --> 00:35:48,760
Tell you, the way he was looking around.

318
00:35:49,220 --> 00:35:54,620
Desperate,like he expected the seventh cavalry.

319
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:57,080
It's a signal.

320
00:35:57,260 --> 00:35:59,980
Undercover says the magic words: "We hit the jackpot"-

321
00:36:00,150 --> 00:36:01,710
the bust goes down.

322
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:04,020
Pete an informant?

323
00:36:04,990 --> 00:36:08,400
Well,Robbery had no undercover ops in the fall of '97,

324
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:11,300
didn't know about the armored car heist until it happened.

325
00:36:11,470 --> 00:36:12,390
But we've got a body mic

326
00:36:12,570 --> 00:36:14,680
and wire checked out of the Communications Unit

327
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:15,740
the day of the robbery,

328
00:36:15,910 --> 00:36:17,140
and guess whose John Hancock

329
00:36:17,310 --> 00:36:19,060
is on the log.

330
00:36:19,230 --> 00:36:21,470
Officer Daniel O'Leary.

331
00:36:22,980 --> 00:36:24,140
O'Leary was a rule-bender.

332
00:36:24,310 --> 00:36:25,150
But dirty?

333
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:27,150
He was obsessed with Pete Doyle.

334
00:36:27,310 --> 00:36:31,070
He put a mic on him,sent him into the heist,then killed him.

335
00:36:31,250 --> 00:36:31,990
That's guesswork.

336
00:36:32,150 --> 00:36:35,060
No body,no evidence, nothing but a signature.

337
00:36:35,230 --> 00:36:38,530
So we pull the equipment, run it for prints,DNA.

338
00:36:38,690 --> 00:36:39,540
Already checked.

339
00:36:39,710 --> 00:36:42,060
Communications threw that stuff out a couple years ago.

340
00:36:42,220 --> 00:36:44,960
Well,O'Leary doesn't know that.

341
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:48,520
Know what this is?

342
00:36:48,690 --> 00:36:50,120
The wire you checked out of Communications

343
00:36:50,300 --> 00:36:52,540
back in September '97.

344
00:36:52,710 --> 00:36:54,820
The one you gave Pete Doyle to wear

345
00:36:54,980 --> 00:36:57,310
day of the armored car robbery.

346
00:36:57,470 --> 00:36:58,940
Sent it to the lab for a work-up.

347
00:36:59,110 --> 00:37:00,580
What do you think they'll find?

348
00:37:00,740 --> 00:37:01,720
What,do you figure you're scaring me

349
00:37:01,890 --> 00:37:04,030
with the smoke and mirrors?

350
00:37:04,190 --> 00:37:05,390
I'm not some mope.

351
00:37:05,550 --> 00:37:07,030
I got 20 years on the job.

352
00:37:07,190 --> 00:37:07,680
True enough.

353
00:37:07,850 --> 00:37:11,060
You were a good cop, maybe a little rough.

354
00:37:11,230 --> 00:37:13,070
All this fuss over that dirtbag?

355
00:37:13,230 --> 00:37:14,710
And I was the only one trying to get

356
00:37:14,870 --> 00:37:16,400
Pete Doyle off the street.

357
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:17,680
The only one who cared.

358
00:37:17,860 --> 00:37:19,730
Yeah,we talked to your old lieutenant.

359
00:37:19,910 --> 00:37:20,910
You tried to get Robbery

360
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:22,580
to investigate Pete and nobody listened.

361
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:23,920
Meanwhile, you were being pushed

362
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:25,220
out of the department.

363
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:27,610
Eh,forced retirement.

364
00:37:27,790 --> 00:37:29,160
My style didn't mesh

365
00:37:29,180 --> 00:37:30,670
anymore.

366
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:31,690
Didn't appreciate you.

367
00:37:31,870 --> 00:37:34,040
You know who complains?

368
00:37:34,200 --> 00:37:37,000
Lowlifes pissed 'cause they got pinched.

369
00:37:37,180 --> 00:37:38,750
And Pete's out there living the life of Reilly.

370
00:37:38,920 --> 00:37:42,920
Eh,crooks get rich, cops get screwed.

371
00:37:43,420 --> 00:37:45,430
We know you were there the day of the heist.

372
00:37:45,590 --> 00:37:48,200
Juries eat this kind of evidence up.

373
00:37:48,380 --> 00:37:50,920
Work with us here; it'll go easier.

374
00:37:51,090 --> 00:37:53,320
You expect me to believe that this is real?

375
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:58,240
I'd stake my career on it, like you did with Pete Doyle.

376
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:10,290
It's hanging heavy on you.

377
00:38:11,380 --> 00:38:15,090
Let it out,O'Leary. It's time.

378
00:38:23,890 --> 00:38:26,040
All those years on the beat.

379
00:38:26,210 --> 00:38:28,190
I was doing good.

380
00:38:28,500 --> 00:38:30,450
I had honor.

381
00:38:32,330 --> 00:38:34,500
Didn't mean anything.

382
00:38:34,670 --> 00:38:36,780
Pete came to you,didn't he?

383
00:38:37,610 --> 00:38:39,920
Full cooperation,

384
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:42,850
as long as his son was left out.

385
00:38:43,010 --> 00:38:43,720
I was supposed to go

386
00:38:43,890 --> 00:38:45,040
to my bosses over it.

387
00:38:45,210 --> 00:38:46,680
But you didn't.

388
00:38:46,860 --> 00:38:48,490
I was halfway out the door,

389
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:52,290
looking at a future with nothing but my pension,

390
00:38:52,450 --> 00:38:54,890
a lifetime of debt.

391
00:38:56,650 --> 00:38:59,460
You ow how much money they keep in those trucks?

392
00:38:59,630 --> 00:39:02,860
You decided to rip him off.

393
00:39:03,750 --> 00:39:05,220
What was he going to do?

394
00:39:05,380 --> 00:39:07,410
Call the cops?

395
00:39:11,530 --> 00:39:12,960
Hey!

396
00:39:15,380 --> 00:39:16,480
Where the hell were you?

397
00:39:16,660 --> 00:39:17,500
The money. Where's the money?

398
00:39:17,670 --> 00:39:19,530
Tommy nearly killed a guy back there!

399
00:39:19,710 --> 00:39:20,450
Where is it,Pete?

400
00:39:20,610 --> 00:39:21,920
It's on the truck where it belongs.

401
00:39:22,090 --> 00:39:23,540
I had the guard hit the panic button.

402
00:39:23,710 --> 00:39:25,530
You were supposed to see this through no matter what.

403
00:39:25,700 --> 00:39:27,090
And you were supposed to stop it,remember?

404
00:39:27,260 --> 00:39:28,410
Before anyone got hurt.

405
00:39:28,570 --> 00:39:29,830
My kid's stepfather was in there,

406
00:39:29,990 --> 00:39:32,290
for crying out loud.

407
00:39:32,470 --> 00:39:33,490
Did he recognize you?

408
00:39:33,660 --> 00:39:35,010
What?

409
00:39:38,860 --> 00:39:40,710
What are you doing?

410
00:39:42,750 --> 00:39:45,190
I can't go down for this.

411
00:39:45,660 --> 00:39:48,130
Why didn't you just get the money?

412
00:39:48,300 --> 00:39:50,250
That's what this was for you.

413
00:39:50,420 --> 00:39:51,150
Money.

414
00:39:51,320 --> 00:39:52,640
Just shut up!

415
00:39:52,810 --> 00:39:54,230
Get down on your knees.

416
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:55,900
Do it.

417
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:05,760
You got ID'd.

418
00:40:06,780 --> 00:40:09,170
Questions are going to come up.

419
00:40:09,620 --> 00:40:12,710
You know what they do to cops in prison?

420
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:16,420
I feel sorry for you,O'Leary.

421
00:40:16,590 --> 00:40:17,610
At least I'm honest.

422
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:20,020
Stop it! I took my second chance.

423
00:40:20,190 --> 00:40:22,830
I did it right, like I said I would.

424
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:23,540
Nothing you do

425
00:40:23,710 --> 00:40:25,820
to me now changes that.

426
00:40:26,110 --> 00:40:28,100
I'm a good man.

427
00:40:28,260 --> 00:40:28,990
What are you?

